race.comment: TINKLEJAZZ (12) is a beautifully bred So You Think filly out of stakes winner Fullazz, making her a full sister to G1 winner D'argento. She has shown encouraging signs at the trials and debuts for the Archibald camp with plenty of expectation. A bright start is anticipated. AGENT ZERO (6) returned with a solid effort at Kembla Grange, sticking on gamely into sixth and not beaten far. He should take improvement from that run and looks better suited stepping up in trip. SIMPLY NUTBUSH (5) was safely held fresh at Nowra when resuming off a long break but had excuses. Drawn better this time and rising to a more suitable journey, she's worth another chance. ONOMA (7), another Archibald debutant, has impressed at the trials with back-to-back wins and should have the tactical speed to offset a wide draw under Collett. Stablemate ALL KIRKED UP (9) hasn't threatened yet but strips fitter and is worth monitoring for improvement.
